---
import ScienceLayout from '../../layouts/ScienceLayout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';

import fitnessLandscape from '../../assets/images/science/palmer-2015-fitness-landscape.jpg';
import delayedCommitment from '../../assets/images/science/palmer-2015-delayed-commitment.jpg';
import evolutionaryDynamics from '../../assets/images/science/chevereau-2015-evolutionary-dynamics.jpg';
---

<ScienceLayout title="Morbidostat | Toprak Lab" description="Build your own morbidostat — an automated high-throughput fluidic system for studying bacterial drug resistance.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="morbidostat-intro">
        The morbidostat is an automated high-throughput fluidic system for studying bacterial drug resistance in dynamically sustained drug environments. By continuously adjusting antibiotic concentrations in response to bacterial growth, it maintains constant selective pressure — enabling direct, real-time observation of resistance evolution.
      </p>

      <div class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__label">Protocol</span>
        <h2 class="article-card__title">Building a morbidostat: an automated continuous-culture device for studying bacterial drug resistance under dynamically sustained drug inhibition</h2>
        <p class="article-card__authors">E. Toprak*, A. Veres, S. Yıldız, J.M. Pedraza, R. Chait, J. Paulsson &amp; R. Kishony*</p>
        <p class="article-card__journal"><em>Nature Protocols</em> <strong>8</strong>, 555–585 (2013)</p>
        <div class="article-card__actions">
          <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/nprot.2013.021" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="article-card__btn">View on Nature.com</a>
          <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/nprot.2013.021.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="article-card__btn article-card__btn--secondary">Download PDF</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="subsection-heading">What It Reveals</h2>
      <p class="subsection-desc">
        Morbidostat experiments produce rich datasets that map the full evolutionary trajectory of resistance — from initial mutations through complex epistatic interactions that shape fitness landscapes.
      </p>

      <figure class="full-figure">
        <Image src={fitnessLandscape} alt="DHFR fitness landscape showing mutation combinations and their resistance levels under trimethoprim selection, with a 3D visualization of all 128 combinatorial variants" width={720} quality={95} densities={[1, 2]} />
        <figcaption>
          <strong>Adaptive landscape of trimethoprim resistance.</strong> Fitness measurements across all combinatorial variants of DHFR mutations reveal the complex topography of resistance evolution — some mutation combinations produce high resistance (tall bars), while others are deleterious despite containing individually beneficial mutations.
          <span class="figure-source">Palmer, Toprak, Baym et al., <em>Nature Communications</em> (2015)</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="full-figure">
        <Image src={delayedCommitment} alt="Delayed commitment to evolutionary fate showing how accessible fitness peaks narrow with successive mutations" width={720} quality={95} densities={[1, 2]} />
        <figcaption>
          <strong>Delayed commitment to evolutionary fate.</strong> Evolving populations maintain access to many fitness peaks early on, but higher-order epistasis progressively narrows their options. A pairwise epistasis model (pink) predicts faster commitment than observed (blue), indicating that complex genetic interactions keep evolutionary options open longer than expected.
          <span class="figure-source">Palmer, Toprak, Baym et al., <em>Nature Communications</em> (2015)</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="subsection-heading">Enabled Research</h2>
      <p class="subsection-desc">
        The morbidostat has enabled a series of studies quantifying the molecular determinants of resistance evolution under diverse drug selection regimes.
      </p>

      <figure class="full-figure">
        <Image src={evolutionaryDynamics} alt="Evolutionary dynamics under nitrofurantoin and chloramphenicol selection showing IC50 trajectories and mutation diversity across replicate populations" width={720} quality={95} densities={[1, 2]} />
        <figcaption>
          <strong>Quantifying evolutionary dynamics under drug selection.</strong> Morbidostat evolution of <em>E. coli</em> under nitrofurantoin (NIT) and chloramphenicol (CHL) reveals distinct resistance trajectories and mutational spectra. Whole-genome sequencing identifies the genes and functional categories driving adaptation to each drug.
          <span class="figure-source">Chevereau, Dravecka, Batur et al., <em>PLOS Biology</em> (2015)</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <ul class="enabled-list">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/ncomms8385" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="enabled-list__title">Delayed commitment to evolutionary fate in antibiotic resistance fitness landscapes</span>
            <span class="enabled-list__meta">Palmer*, Toprak*, Baym et al. — <em>Nature Communications</em>, 2015</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosbiology/article?id=10.1371/journal.pbio.1002299" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="enabled-list__title">Quantifying the determinants of evolutionary dynamics leading to drug resistance</span>
            <span class="enabled-list__meta">Chevereau, Dravecka, Batur et al. — <em>PLOS Biology</em>, 2015</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://journals.plos.org/plosbiology/article?id=10.1371/journal.pbio.1002552" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="enabled-list__title">Sequence-specific targeting of bacterial resistance genes increases antibiotic efficacy</span>
            <span class="enabled-list__meta">Ayhan, Tamer, Akbar et al. — <em>PLOS Biology</em>, 2016</span>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-021-23191-z" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span class="enabled-list__title">A trimethoprim derivative impedes antibiotic resistance evolution</span>
            <span class="enabled-list__meta">Manna, Tamer, Gaszek et al. — <em>Nature Communications</em>, 2021</span>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</ScienceLayout>

<style>
  .section {
    padding-block: 1.25rem;
  }

  .morbidostat-intro {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: var(--size-md);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .subsection-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--size-xl);
    font-weight: 400;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: normal;
    color: var(--color-gray-900);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .subsection-desc {
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .full-figure {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-100);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .full-figure img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .full-figure figcaption {
    padding: 0.625rem 1rem;
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
    line-height: 1.5;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-gray-100);
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .full-figure figcaption strong {
    color: var(--color-gray-900);
  }

  .figure-source {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.375rem;
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--color-gray-300);
  }

  .article-card {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-gray-100);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
  }

  .article-card__label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-navy-light);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .article-card__title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--size-lg);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-900);
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: normal;
  }

  .article-card__authors {
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .article-card__journal {
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .article-card__actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .article-card__btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.5rem;
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-navy);
    color: var(--color-white);
    background-color: var(--color-navy);
    transition: background-color 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .article-card__btn:hover {
    background-color: var(--color-navy-light);
    border-color: var(--color-navy-light);
  }

  .article-card__btn--secondary {
    color: var(--color-navy);
    background-color: transparent;
  }

  .article-card__btn--secondary:hover {
    color: var(--color-white);
    background-color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  /* Enabled research list */
  .enabled-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .enabled-list li {
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .enabled-list li:hover {
    border-left-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .enabled-list a {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.875rem 0 0.875rem 0.75rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-gray-100);
  }

  .enabled-list li:last-child a {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .enabled-list__title {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: var(--size-sm);
    color: var(--color-gray-900);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .enabled-list a:hover .enabled-list__title {
    color: var(--color-navy-light);
  }

  .enabled-list__meta {
    display: block;
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--color-gray-300);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article-card {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
